   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">Follow this procedure to switch the burner cooling water booster pumps:</p>
      </context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To switch the burner cooling water booster pumps:</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Go to the PVAG control panel located behind the Tank 1 &amp; 2 control
                     room.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Click on <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Settings</uicontrol>.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Click on <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Pump settings</uicontrol>.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Click on <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Change pumps now</uicontrol>.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">One burner cooling water booster pump will automatically turn on when burner
                     cooling water flow drops below the low limit.</li>
               </ul>
               <note type="note" id="note_y3w_vkd_5cc" class="- topic/note ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Pumps should be in Automatic mode with automatic switchover enabled during
                     normal operation.</p>
               </note>
